                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/26.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chinese today commenced registering with me in books of the Chinese Republic and
                    presenting their cédulas for personal examination. <pb facs="1231" n="1127"
                        xml:id="pg_1127"/> This expression of confidence gives first hope for
                    satisfactory solution of problem. Law 50 suspended pending registration. Chinese
                    in meeting at Panama and Colon request my continuance in charge of their
                    interests at least pending outcome of present plan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wicker</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
